24
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:11,920
If you know me this well

25
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:14,440
then you must know what I'm thinking.

26
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Ai Cir.

27
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:24,440
Ai Cir.

28
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Ai Cir.

29
00:04:37,360 --> 00:04:38,600
Phu and I are together.

30
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,520
Since when?

31
00:04:44,640 --> 00:04:46,120
- In my dream.
- What?

32
00:04:46,880 --> 00:04:47,880
In your dream?

33
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:52,720
- You’re saying you’re his boyfriend—
- In my dreams.

34
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,960
Yes, I dreamed about it.

35
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,120
Ai Wim.

36
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:07,920
If you like someone so much
that you dream about them

37
00:05:08,480 --> 00:05:09,920
seeing them as your lover

38
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:13,880
seeing yourself being
with them since high school

39
00:05:14,360 --> 00:05:17,800
experiencing happiness
you never dared to dream of...

40
00:05:20,480 --> 00:05:21,480
what would you do?

41
00:05:28,360 --> 00:05:31,880
So that's why you said he was
your boyfriend when you woke up.

42
00:05:34,480 --> 00:05:35,480
Wait a minute.

43
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:41,840
Don’t tell me you actually told
him that, and he believed you?

44
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:45,520
No, I didn’t tell him about the dream.

45
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,320
Shit.

46
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:53,080
Don’t tell me that you told
him you’re from a parallel world.

47
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,920
Ai Cir.

48
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,800
Hi there.

49
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,640
Hey! Why are you with Phu, Ai Zone?

50
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,600
Why are you here?

51
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:44,880
I heard about Mom.

52
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:48,360
You know that Dad and I are
keeping an eye on her secretary.

53
00:06:48,840 --> 00:06:49,840
Does Dad even care?

54
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,360
Brother.

55
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,200
But you shouldn’t have approached Phu.

56
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:08,440
I was just worried.

57
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,040
P’ Cir.

58
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,120
I’m fine.

59
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:18,000
Why don’t you come in?

60
00:07:23,560 --> 00:07:26,600
Hey, wait for me!
You can’t just leave me out of this.

61
00:07:40,640 --> 00:07:41,840
Are you okay, Phu?

62
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,840
It’s my mom, right?

63
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,120
What happened?

64
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,000
Mom sent someone to deal with Phu.

65
00:07:56,720 --> 00:08:01,920
She sent someone to ask how much
money he’d want to break up with you.

66
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:03,520
What?

67
00:08:03,520 --> 00:08:06,560
Damn it, I fucking knew someone
like her wouldn’t just stay put.

68
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,000
I think Mom’s targeting Phu.

69
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:13,800
Why do you think that?

70
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:24,960
You know that this guy is
Ai Cir’s younger brother, right?

71
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:26,600
As for that hag—

72
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:29,680
Uh, no.

73
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:33,280
Uh, their mother’s a total psycho.

74
00:08:33,760 --> 00:08:36,600
Back when their parents still loved
each other, she was already crazy.

75
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:39,559
She treated their dad like
he was her personal property.

76
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:43,039
He couldn’t do anything or talk to anyone.

77
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,520
But he put up with it.

78
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:50,680
Well, until...

79
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:57,320
Mom harassed our elementary school teacher

80
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,080
until she committed suicide.

81
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:11,800
Is being just a teacher not
enough to make ends meet

82
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:16,240
that you have to spread your legs
for someone else’s husband?

83
00:09:16,840 --> 00:09:19,000
In public, you're committed to education.

84
00:09:19,400 --> 00:09:24,360
But how many parents have you
sold yourself to behind closed doors?

85
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,640
That's not true. I’d never do that.

86
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,840
Really?

87
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:30,880
Are you saying what I saw isn’t true?

88
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:34,760
Since you dare to mess
with someone like me.

89
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:36,760
Get up. Now.

90
00:09:39,240 --> 00:09:43,360
You really want to know
what hell is like, don’t you?

91
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:47,880
That hag incited the parent
association, bribed the school.

92
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:51,040
Sawasdee ka, take care on your way home.

93
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,040
Prink, you bitch. Whore!

94
00:09:53,720 --> 00:09:57,360
You’ve got me, but you’re
still whoring yourself out!

95
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,760
What are you talking about?
Who are you?

96
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:01,480
But their dad knew nothing about it.

97
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,200
He thought that if he
never saw the teacher again

98
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:06,000
that hag would calm down.

99
00:10:07,160 --> 00:10:08,280
The fuck are you looking at!

100
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:11,560
Are you curious? Then I’ll tell you.

101
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:14,680
This bitch is a fucking whore!

102
00:10:15,560 --> 00:10:16,840
You better watch your husbands!

103
00:10:17,800 --> 00:10:20,120
No, it’s not like that.

104
00:10:20,800 --> 00:10:23,600
It’s not what you think.
It’s not true.

105
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:25,760
No.

106
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,360
But…

107
00:10:28,280 --> 00:10:29,600
We can’t let a hooker teach our children.

108
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:30,760
Send her back to the brothel.

109
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,240
Even as a teacher, she’s still a whore.

110
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,760
The principal should take care of this.

111
00:10:34,080 --> 00:10:35,760
Resignation Letter

112
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,360
He only found out later when...

113
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:50,520
the teacher was longer in this world.

114
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:02,120
That’s when Uncle said he wanted a divorce.

115
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:06,720
So what happened next?
Did P’ Cir’s mom agree to it?

116
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:11,760
You think she would? She
went nuts and attacked these two.

117
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:14,440
Ordering people to beat her
own kids in front of their dad.

118
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:18,800
And she was satisfied seeing
him unable to do anything.

119
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,520
She declared that if he wanted a divorce

120
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,680
he had to leave one of them with her.

121
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:28,840
But you know what the one left
behind has to go through, right?

122
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:32,400
So…

123
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,600
Your dad chose P’ Zone.

124
00:11:44,640 --> 00:11:45,800
He made the right choice.

125
00:11:47,040 --> 00:11:48,040
Zone’s younger than me.

126
00:11:50,400 --> 00:11:54,400
But just because you're older doesn’t
mean you're stronger or tougher.

127
00:11:55,320 --> 00:11:56,880
You were only eight years old.

128
00:11:58,400 --> 00:11:59,400
I’m okay.

129
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,440
Alright.

130
00:12:08,280 --> 00:12:11,440
You can probably imagine what
that hag is capable of by now.

131
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:14,960
She doesn’t see Ai Cir as her son.

132
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,240
He’s merely a tool for revenge.

133
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:20,080
Just a showpiece for her status.

134
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:24,480
I bet you can’t imagine
what Ai Cir had to bargain for

135
00:12:24,720 --> 00:12:26,240
just to get out and live on his own.

136
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,600
What did you trade for that?

137
00:12:38,640 --> 00:12:39,760
My entire life’s freedom.

138
00:12:43,440 --> 00:12:44,560
What does it mean?

139
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:48,920
It means he traded
his four years of university

140
00:12:48,920 --> 00:12:50,840
for the rest of his life.

141
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:54,800
After graduation, he’s got
no right to disobey anymore.

142
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,880
Damn it, how could you accept that, Ai Cir?

143
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:59,640
You’re not an eight-year-old anymore!

144
00:12:59,680 --> 00:13:01,000
Fight back, damn it!

145
00:13:01,520 --> 00:13:02,920
I agree with P’ Wim.

146
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,720
Things are different now.

147
00:13:06,440 --> 00:13:07,880
And Dad has changed as well.

148
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:10,720
Negotiating is useless.

149
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,560
- But I think—
- Zone.

150
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:16,880
No, I don’t agree with you.

151
00:13:18,560 --> 00:13:19,880
You have your own life.

152
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:23,960
You can live your life.
No need to give it up for anyone.

153
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,320
When my dad passed away

154
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:32,680
he told me that he wanted me
to live the happiest life I could.

155
00:13:33,800 --> 00:13:35,120
Because my life is mine to live.

156
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,760
He said not to get stuck in sorrow.

157
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:40,920
You too, P’ Cir.

158
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,240
You have to live a happy life.

159
00:13:45,040 --> 00:13:46,320
You can’t just throw it away.

160
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:00,520
I’m okay.

161
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:03,560
I’m so frustrated.

162
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:07,000
I’m frustrated for you.

163
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:11,400
Thank you.

164
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:23,640
It might’ve been useless
back then, but not now.

165
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:27,000
What are you trying to say?

166
00:14:28,040 --> 00:14:30,200
I never had a purpose in life.

167
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:32,480
Until I met Phu.

168
00:14:41,920 --> 00:14:43,600
If I hadn’t met you in high school

169
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:46,320
I wouldn’t have had
the guts to leave that house.

170
00:14:48,400 --> 00:14:50,000
And I won’t go back.

171
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:55,520
Because I have someone I want to be with.

172
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:00,480
What can I do to help you?

173
00:15:09,880 --> 00:15:11,160
Why don’t you just date Ai Cir?

174
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:17,200
Well, if you want to rebel,
then rebel all the way.

175
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:18,720
Make your mom restless.

176
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:22,280
And things aren’t the same as
back then. Times have changed.

177
00:15:22,800 --> 00:15:24,840
She can’t just do whatever
she wants anymore.

178
00:15:25,400 --> 00:15:27,600
She’s got money, and so do you.

179
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:30,720
If she dares to hire people,
then hire some back.

180
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:33,840
Lure her out to make
her show her real intentions.

181
00:15:35,200 --> 00:15:36,640
I can't use Phu as bait.

182
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,240
Why not?

183
00:15:39,080 --> 00:15:40,440
Do you realize what you just said?

184
00:15:41,160 --> 00:15:45,320
Of course, I know I’m
making myself a bigger target.

185
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:48,880
But so what? Why should I be afraid?

186
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:50,920
I agree with P’ Wim.

187
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:55,040
Let’s show her that
you have your own life too.

188
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:59,880
And honestly, I’m so pissed
she threw money at me like that.

189
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:02,280
- Phu.
- Don’t ‘Phu’ me.

190
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:08,640
I really like your brother’s boyfriend.

191
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:12,040
I’m with you on that one.

192
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:25,640
Next time, give me a
heads-up before you come.

193
00:16:28,360 --> 00:16:29,680
Worried about the one upstairs?

194
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:34,080
I always just show up.
Never call ahead before.

195
00:16:34,960 --> 00:16:35,960
At least you’re aware.

196
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:39,160
Even if you’re my brother,
I won’t give him to you.

197
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:44,080
P’ Cir.

198
00:16:47,840 --> 00:16:48,880
Dad worries about you.

199
00:16:56,840 --> 00:16:59,280
Then go tell him not to worry.

200
00:17:01,480 --> 00:17:02,600
Are you still mad at him?

201
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:08,920
You know that he’s always
felt guilty about what happened.

202
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,400
Especially about you.

203
00:17:19,079 --> 00:17:20,800
Tell him to get over it already.

204
00:17:21,560 --> 00:17:23,040
It’s been years now.

205
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:27,000
- Can’t you just get mad at me instead?
- Zone.

206
00:17:27,040 --> 00:17:30,320
If I were older than you,
or if I’d been born before you

207
00:17:31,400 --> 00:17:33,320
you wouldn’t have had
to suffer at Mom’s hands.

208
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:34,320
Ozone.

209
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:41,240
Even if I were younger
or had been born after you

210
00:17:42,080 --> 00:17:44,640
I’d never let you stay with that woman.

211
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:48,640
It’s better that it’s me.

212
00:17:56,360 --> 00:18:01,680
Tell Dad that I’ll drop by if I have time.

213
00:18:15,040 --> 00:18:16,280
It’s my turn now, Brother.

214
00:18:24,840 --> 00:18:26,000
Are you mad at me, P’ Cir?

215
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:28,920
Because you were too impulsive.

216
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,480
I just wanted to help.

217
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:35,320
I can’t stand the way she’s treating you.

218
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:37,520
That’s not family.

219
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:40,440
To me, family wouldn’t do that.

220
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,960
But she’s capable of more than you think.

221
00:18:45,440 --> 00:18:46,440
I’m not afraid.

222
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:49,920
P’ Wim said that after what
happened to your teacher

223
00:18:50,160 --> 00:18:51,920
she hasn’t done
anything so blatantly since.

224
00:18:53,520 --> 00:18:54,560
That’s true.

225
00:18:55,280 --> 00:18:56,560
She lost a lot because of that.

226
00:18:57,520 --> 00:19:01,760
But it’s a different matter from
you agreeing to Ai Wim’s offer.

227
00:19:03,040 --> 00:19:04,040
What offer?

228
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:08,600
The one where I’m
supposed to live with you.

229
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:13,440
Well, P’ Wim said your mom might hire
someone to stay in the rooms next to ours.

230
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:16,920
If you want to convince her,
you’ll have to do what P’ Wim said.

231
00:19:18,720 --> 00:19:20,600
Let’s go. You still
have to pack your stuff.

232
00:19:29,040 --> 00:19:30,840
Since you guys are already a couple

233
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:32,280
why not just move in together?

234
00:19:32,360 --> 00:19:35,200
That way, you wouldn’t have to
worry about someone hurting Phu.

235
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:36,920
I’m doing you a favor here, you know.

236
00:19:57,920 --> 00:19:58,920
Let me help.

237
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:08,240
Are you really sure you
want me to stay here?

238
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:10,400
Of course.

239
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:13,000
I guess.

240
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Stubborn.

241
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:17,040
Stubborn to help you.

242
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:23,720
If you keep this up, you'll lose
your virginity without realizing it.

243
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:27,280
You won’t do anything to me.

244
00:20:28,040 --> 00:20:28,800
Right?

245
00:20:28,840 --> 00:20:30,200
Did I do anything last time?

246
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,040
You said it was for nursing.

247
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,680
Now I’ll say we’re a couple.

248
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:43,200
So I guess I can... do it now.

249
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:53,360
Right?

250
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:06,160
Wait, P’Cir.

251
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,760
P' Cir, hold on.

252
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:27,760
Phukan.

253
00:21:33,040 --> 00:21:34,040
Scared of me now?

254
00:21:38,240 --> 00:21:41,000
Why should I be scared?
This is no big deal.

255
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:52,160
Go ahead. Go for it.

256
00:21:57,120 --> 00:21:59,560
Come on. Just do it. Go ahead.

257
00:22:11,840 --> 00:22:13,000
Stubborn kid.

258
00:22:14,120 --> 00:22:16,200
Don’t cry later if it actually happens.

259
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,000
